cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.NI 

This paper is about developing a new Android malware detection approach using deep learning and static analysis. The paper focuses on the use of graph representation learning for malware detection, which falls under the category of network representation learning. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as graph convolutional networks, which falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the analysis of source code and the creation of higher-level graphical semantics, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper involves the use of mobile devices and applications, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
